    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in rrc_deliver_ue_ctxt_release_cmd function\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_deliver_ue_ctxt_release_cmd` function in the gNB RRC module was allocating memory for the `rrc_container` byte array but never freeing it, leading to memory leaks during UE context release procedures. This issue became apparent when running long-term stress tests with multiple UEs connecting and disconnecting.\n\nThe root cause was that while the function properly allocated memory for the `byte_array_t` structure and its buffer, there was no corresponding free operation in the code path that handles the UE context release command. This fix ensures that the allocated memory is properly freed after it has been processed by the lower layers.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB.c`: Added proper memory deallocation for the `rrc_container` byte array in `rrc_deliver_ue_ctxt_release_cmd` function.\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB.c`: Updated function documentation to clarify memory management responsibilities.\n\n"
}